[According to the figures of the Dutch National Institute for Public
Health and the Environment (RIVM), the number of human infections
with Q fever, since the start of this epidemic in mid 2007, is 3313
(2007: N=168, 2008: N=1000, 2009: N=2145). Out of the 2145 cases
reported so far during 2009, 2047 have been laboratory confirmed, 98
suspected; 5 died. An epicurve can be seen at
<http://www.rivm.nl/cib/binaries/epicurve%20Q-koorts_tcm92-59728.pdf#%20class=>.

Further data, including an outbreak map, graphics, 'Information for
professionals' and several presentations on the disease in man and
animal (in Dutch), are available at
<http://www.rivm.nl/cib/themas/Q-koorts/>).

The Dutch Q fever outbreak is the largest of its kind on record. - Mod.AS].

[The Netherlands can be located using the HealthMap/ProMEDmail
interactive map at:
<http://healthmap.org/r/00S1>.
- CopyEd.EJP]
